The Bay Area continues to build train stations that have terrible connections to buses. The transfer from a @TriDeltaTransit bus to the Pittsburg Center @SFBART station, which opened in 2018, takes over 5 minutes and requires crossing a dangerous busy intersection. https://t.co/vsX42zGo2U

The #SeamlessTransitAct seeks to eliminate key barriers to ridership:
1. Different fare structures
2. Uncoordinated schedules "that make transferring from one system to another an exercise in frustration" 
3. A confusing muddle of transit maps
